dict.string: If you can draw a graph of your code, then the code will be able to run no matter what.
In addition to type safety, node based programming makes it simpler to visualize programs, therefore making it easier to catch bugs.

Most programming lanugages use English keywords like if and while, which is hard for foreign language speakers to understand. Visual programs can be represented without using any keywords, so anybody from around the world can write visual programs.
While traditional code requires a keyboard, visual programs can be written using many more modern input devices, including touch, mice, styli, and even virtual reality.
